On March 30, 2020, President Donald J. Trump issued a statement to extend the national emergency declared on April 1, 2015, due to the increasing prevalence and severity of malicious cyber-enabled activities originating from outside the United States. The national emergency, declared under the International Emergency Economic Powers Act, is aimed at addressing the threat posed to national security, foreign policy, and the economy. The extension of the national emergency is in accordance with the National Emergencies Act and will be effective for one year.